OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FTV executive Samir Shah    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fchosen as new BBC chairman 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, TV executive Samir Shah has been named 
OL,6, as the government's choice for the new 
OL,7, BBC chairman, following Richard Sharp's
OL,8, resignation in April.                  
OL,10,FMr Shah, 71, previously held a series  
OL,11,Fof roles at the BBC, including as its  
OL,12,Fhead of current affairs.               
OL,14,FIn a statement, he said he was         
OL,15,F"delighted" to have been named the     
OL,16,Fgovernment's preferred candidate.      
OL,18,FMr Sharp resigned earlier this year    
OL,19,Fafter breaking rules over dealings with
OL,20,FBoris Johnson ahead of his appointment.
